{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nR1 (asserted-capability grounding probe) edits the Pass-1 finder rubric, so it changes what\nEVERY plan review surfaces ‚Äî not a niche path. Before R1 (or any gate candidate, e.g. R5's\nverifier change) is exposed to production, we must measure how much it perturbs the verdicts of\nplans that already passed the gate and closed without trouble. E3 is the counterfactual replay\nthat produces that measurement; together with E2 (seeded-defect benchmark) it is the evidence R1\nis gated on.\n\nThe gate this feeds has a hard false-positive bar. Per `docs/research/task-decomposition-sota-2026.md`\n¬ß5 / R1 (lines ~163-169), R1 FAILs if, on **30 sampled historical plans that PASSed and closed with\nzero post-claim edits**, **>3/30 (10%)** gain a new *blocking* finding, or the **median new-advisory\ncount rises by >1 per review**. The epic additionally reports a corroborating aggregate: the\n**PASS‚ÜíBLOCK flip rate ‚â§2%** on the wider cleanly-closed sample. This ticket produces both, plus a\nverdict-transition matrix and per-criterion finding deltas so a candidate's churn is attributable.\n\nA scoring-only replay (re-classifying the persisted sidecar findings without new LLM calls) is\n**insufficient for the candidate side**: R-candidates change the Pass-1 finder prompt, so they change\n*what is surfaced*, not only *how a surfaced finding is scored*. The candidate side must therefore be a\nfull pipeline re-run. The **baseline side stays the zero-cost persisted sidecar** (see What) ‚Äî so this\nis the cheapest faithful design, not a gratuitous double run.\n\n## What\n\n**Definitions (pinned; these resolve the block themes).**\n\n1. **Cleanly-closed ticket** ‚Äî an explicit filter over `outcome_corpus.jsonl` (628 rows; schema in\n   `runs/README.md:53-88`), using verified field names:\n   `post_claim_edit_class == \"none\"` **AND** `reopen_count == 0` **AND** `force_close == false`.\n   (No substantive post-claim plan edit, no reopen, no force-close.) This filter is encoded in the\n   replay driver, not left to the analyst. Requiring `post_claim_edit_class == \"none\"` is load-bearing:\n   it removes the ~8.3% post-claim plan-text drift (README ¬ß5.2) that would otherwise inflate spurious\n   PASS‚ÜíBLOCK flips.\n\n2. **Baseline verdict source** ‚Äî the outcome corpus has **no verdict field**; the baseline is the\n   persisted `REVIEW_RESULT` sidecar, read via `rebar.llm.plan_review.sidecar.all_review_results(tid)`\n   (returns every retained round newest‚Üíoldest). For each sampled ticket the baseline is **one round**:\n   the **most-recent round whose `impact_model_version == \"plan-v3\"`** (the current\n   `sidecar.IMPACT_MODEL_VERSION`) **and whose `verdict ‚àà {PASS, BLOCK}`** (INDETERMINATE rounds are\n   skipped when choosing the baseline round). From that one round we read `verdict` (sidecar.py:482 ‚Üí\n   `baseline_verdict`), `material_fingerprint` (the plan-text hash), `model`, and its\n   `findings[]` filtered to surfaced by `sidecar.surfaced_findings` (`decision ‚àà {\"block\",\"advisory\"}`).\n   Using a single round (not a cross-round union) keeps the baseline's verdict, findings, and material\n   fingerprint mutually consistent so they compare against the single candidate run. Fixing the cohort\n   to `plan-v3` satisfies ADR 0036 (never pool findings across `impact_model_version`); the driver\n   asserts the candidate build's `sidecar.IMPACT_MODEL_VERSION` equals the baseline cohort version and\n   fails loud otherwise.\n\n3. **Frozen baseline artifact** ‚Äî step 0 of the driver freezes the baseline for every sampled ticket\n   into `runs/e3/baseline.jsonl` (committed) **before any candidate run**. All downstream comparison\n   reads this file, never live sidecars, so the baseline is immutable, reproducible, and immune to any\n   sidecar the candidate run might emit.\n\n4. **Plan-text drift control (material fingerprint match).** `orchestrator.material_fingerprint`\n   (pass1.py:551) hashes only `{ticket_id, description, file_impact, children}` ‚Äî plan material, not\n   code SHA. The candidate run reads current ticket text via `assemble_context`, so it emits its own\n   `material_fingerprint`. A ticket enters the matrix **only if the candidate-run material fingerprint\n   equals the frozen baseline material fingerprint** ‚Äî guaranteeing every counted (baseline, candidate)\n   pair is over byte-identical plan material, so a verdict flip is attributable to the candidate change +\n   LLM sampling noise, never to text drift. Mismatches are excluded and counted separately.\n\n**The replay.** Drive the **candidate branch build's** gate over the sample via\n`review_plan(tid, source=\"local\", repo_root=‚Ä¶, sign=False, emit_sidecar=False, force=True)`\n(signature `rebar.llm.plan_review.review_plan`; the entrypoint `rebar review-plan` calls; the\n`ProductionBatchRunner` seam backs it), capturing each returned verdict dict ‚Äî `verdict`,\n`material_fingerprint`, and full `findings[]` ‚Äî to `runs/e3/<candidate>/raw_verdicts.jsonl`. The\nexact non-mutating replay flags are load-bearing: **`emit_sidecar=False`** (the default `True`\nwould append a new `REVIEW_RESULT` to every sampled ticket, mutating the store and polluting the\nvery corpus E1/R7 read), **`sign=False`** (no attestation for a throwaway replay), and\n**`force=True`** (the default `force=False` lets `_run_plan_review`'s idempotent-reuse\nshort-circuit return the *prior* verdict instead of actually re-running the candidate gate).\n`REBAR_SYNC_PUSH=off` additionally guarantees no push. The existing `harnesses/run_review_*.py`\nbatch drivers are the precedent: iterate the ticket set, checkpoint per ticket (atomic append) so\na mid-run stop resumes without re-processing, and assert `len(raw_verdicts) == len(sample)` before\nany summary is written.\n\n**Verdict ‚Üí matrix mapping.** Cells are `(baseline_verdict, candidate_verdict)` over\n`{PASS, BLOCK}¬≤`: PASS‚ÜíPASS / PASS‚ÜíBLOCK / BLOCK‚ÜíPASS / BLOCK‚ÜíBLOCK. A **candidate** verdict that is\nINDETERMINATE (LLM outage / mid-run degradation ‚Äî ¬ß5.1 shows ~8% of reviews land INDETERMINATE) or a\nmaterial-fingerprint mismatch is **excluded** from the matrix and every flip-rate denominator, and its\ncount is reported in a separate `excluded` block. Baseline INDETERMINATE rounds never become a baseline\n(see def 2), so the baseline column is always PASS or BLOCK. The matrix is **segmented by\n`impact_model_version`** (one sub-matrix per version; here a single `plan-v3` segment).\n\n**Primary metric (PASS‚ÜíBLOCK flip rate ‚â§2%).**\n`flip_rate = |{PASS‚ÜíBLOCK}| / |{tickets with baseline_verdict == PASS, included}|` ‚Äî the false-block\nrate on plans that legitimately passed and closed cleanly. Recorded per candidate; the epic bar is\n‚â§ 0.02.\n\n**Primary R1 gate (SOTA ¬ß5/R1, higher-rigor).** On the **30-plan FP-control subset** (def below), R1\nFAILs if the **median across N=3 candidate replays** of (a) count of subset plans gaining ‚â•1 new\n*blocking* finding is **>3/30**, or (b) the per-review new-advisory-count delta has **median >1**. \"New\"\n= a candidate surfaced finding whose `norm_id` (sidecar.py:261, reword-tolerant, criterion-scoped) is\nabsent from that ticket's frozen baseline surfaced findings. The N=3 median (worst-case also reported)\nis the LLM-nondeterminism control ‚Äî see below.\n\n**LLM nondeterminism control (honest, and bounded in cost).** The production gate has **no\ntemperature/seed knob** (`LLMConfig` exposes neither; `docs/experiments/plan-review-chunking-budget.md`\nnotes it runs at default temperature for natural repeat-variance), and adding one is a `src/rebar`\nchange this experiment must not make. So determinism is bought statistically, and cost is concentrated\nwhere the gate decision is made:\n- **Baseline = frozen sidecar ‚Üí 0 LLM calls.**\n- **Full ~200 transition matrix ‚Üí one candidate replay** (the descriptive artifact; its ‚â§2% figure\n  carries a stated single-shot noise caveat).\n- **30-plan FP-control subset ‚Üí N=3 candidate replays**, metric taken at the **median** (worst-case\n  reported), *plus a null-replay noise floor*: the **current/unmodified build** is also run once over the\n  same 30 plans, and its PASS‚ÜíBLOCK flips vs the frozen baseline (identical material) quantify the gate's\n  intrinsic verdict noise on identical inputs. R1's flips are read against that floor.\nThis keeps replication on the 30 plans that gate R1, not the expensive 200. Total billable candidate\nruns ‚âà 200 (matrix) + 3√ó30 (FP replication) + 30 (null floor).\n\n**Per-criterion finding delta schema (concrete).** For attribution, the driver emits\n`runs/e3/<candidate>/criterion_deltas.jsonl` ‚Äî one row per **(ticket_id, criterion)** over the union of\ncriteria cited in that ticket's baseline-surfaced ‚à™ candidate-surfaced findings ‚Äî with exactly these\nkeys:\n- `ticket_id` (str)\n- `criterion` (str)\n- `baseline_surfaced_count` (int) ‚Äî baseline surfaced findings citing this criterion\n- `candidate_surfaced_count` (int)\n- `baseline_blocking_count` (int) ‚Äî subset with `decision == \"block\"`\n- `candidate_blocking_count` (int)\n- `net_surfaced_delta` (int) ‚Äî `candidate_surfaced_count ‚àí baseline_surfaced_count`\n- `net_blocking_delta` (int) ‚Äî `candidate_blocking_count ‚àí baseline_blocking_count`\n- `new_norm_ids` (sorted list[str]) ‚Äî `norm_id`s in candidate-surfaced-for-criterion but not baseline\n- `removed_norm_ids` (sorted list[str]) ‚Äî `norm_id`s in baseline-surfaced-for-criterion but not candidate\nFindings join across the two builds on **`norm_id`** (the exact-text `id` differs across builds by\nconstruction ‚Äî sidecar.py:247-257). A rollup `runs/e3/<candidate>/criterion_deltas_summary.json`\naggregates the same fields per criterion across the sample, so an R-row's churn is attributable to\nspecific criteria.\n\n**Stratified sampling frame (reproducible).**\n- Eligible pool = `outcome_corpus.jsonl` rows passing the cleanly-closed filter **AND** having a usable\n  `plan-v3` baseline round (def 2). `verdict` and `model` (absent from the corpus) are recovered by\n  joining each ticket's frozen baseline round on `ticket_id`.\n- Draw **~200** stratified by `(ticket_type √ó baseline_verdict)`, **proportional** to the eligible-pool\n  distribution with a **floor of 5 per non-empty cell** (cells below floor collapse into the same\n  ticket_type's larger verdict cell). Deterministic: `random.Random(1729).sample(...)` (the seed the\n  repo's existing samplers use ‚Äî README ¬ß2 / `build_adjudication_corpus.py`). `model` and overlay\n  signals are recorded per sampled row as attributes (for later ADR-0036 segmentation) but are not\n  allocation axes, since plan-v3 sidecars share the production model.\n- **FP-control 30-subset** = deterministic `random.Random(1729)` draw of 30 tickets from the\n  **baseline_verdict == PASS** members of the 200-sample (a genuine subset; matches SOTA \"PASSed +\n  closed + zero post-claim edits\", already guaranteed by cleanly-closed). Written to\n  `runs/e3/fp_control_sample.jsonl`.\n\n## Scope\n\n- **`docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/`**: `replay_candidate.py` (driver with `sample` /\n  `run --candidate <label>` / `analyze --candidate <label>` / `--verify` subcommands) and\n  `e3_metrics.py` (pure, LLM-free functions: `build_matrix`, `criterion_deltas`,\n  `pass_to_block_flip_rate`, `fp_control_eval`).\n- **`docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/e3/`**: committed `sample.jsonl`, `fp_control_sample.jsonl`,\n  `baseline.jsonl`, and per-candidate `<candidate>/{raw_verdicts.jsonl, transition_matrix.json,\n  criterion_deltas.jsonl, criterion_deltas_summary.json, fp_control.json}`.\n- **`docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/README.md`**: an E3 section documenting the method (baseline\n  source + chosen round, cleanly-closed filter, material-fingerprint drift control, nondeterminism\n  control + cost, INDETERMINATE handling, the R1 verdict for the candidate run).\n- **`tests/unit/test_e3_metrics.py`**: a CI-collectable golden test for the pure `e3_metrics` functions\n  over a tiny fixture.\n- **No `src/rebar` behavior change** ‚Äî E3 is measurement, not a gate change. Candidate rubric/registry\n  edits live on the candidate's own experiment branch build (per operator direction; no overlay/config\n  flag). Live LLM calls are billable and run once per candidate by the executor; every proving command\n  below re-derives the summaries **offline** from committed `raw_verdicts.jsonl` + `baseline.jsonl`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The stratified ~200-ticket sample and the frozen baseline are committed and reproducible: every\n  sampled row satisfies the cleanly-closed filter, and `baseline.jsonl` carries a `plan-v3`\n  `baseline_verdict ‚àà {PASS,BLOCK}` + `material_fingerprint` per ticket.\n  Proving: `python docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/replay_candidate.py sample --verify`\n  (offline; re-derives sample + baseline and exits non-zero unless byte-identical to the committed\n  files), then\n  `jq -e 'select(.post_claim_edit_class!=\"none\" or .reopen_count!=0 or .force_close!=false)' docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/e3/sample.jsonl | head -c1 | ( ! grep -q . )`\n  (no row violates the filter) and\n  `test $(wc -l < docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/e3/fp_control_sample.jsonl) -eq 30`.\n\n- [ ] The verdict-transition matrix is committed, segmented by `impact_model_version`, and internally\n  consistent. Proving:\n  `python docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/replay_candidate.py analyze --candidate <label> --verify`\n  (offline; recomputes `transition_matrix.json` from committed `raw_verdicts.jsonl` + `baseline.jsonl`\n  and asserts equality) and the cardinality check\n  `jq -e '.segments[] | (.cells.pass_to_pass + .cells.pass_to_block + .cells.block_to_pass + .cells.block_to_block + .excluded.total) == .observed_total' docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/e3/<label>/transition_matrix.json`.\n\n- [ ] The per-criterion finding deltas are committed with the pinned schema. Proving:\n  `jq -e 'has(\"ticket_id\") and has(\"criterion\") and has(\"baseline_surfaced_count\") and has(\"candidate_surfaced_count\") and has(\"baseline_blocking_count\") and has(\"candidate_blocking_count\") and has(\"net_surfaced_delta\") and has(\"net_blocking_delta\") and (.new_norm_ids|type==\"array\") and (.removed_norm_ids|type==\"array\")' docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/e3/<label>/criterion_deltas.jsonl`\n  (every row carries the schema) and `pytest tests/unit/test_e3_metrics.py -k delta -q` (golden proves\n  `criterion_deltas` joins baseline‚Üîcandidate on `norm_id` correctly).\n\n- [ ] The PASS‚ÜíBLOCK flip rate is computed on the cleanly-closed PASS-baseline denominator and recorded\n  per candidate. Proving: `pytest tests/unit/test_e3_metrics.py -k flip -q` (golden proves\n  `pass_to_block_flip_rate` = |PASS‚ÜíBLOCK| / |included PASS-baseline|) and\n  `jq -e 'has(\"flip_rate\") and (.flip_rate|type==\"number\")' docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/e3/<label>/fp_control.json`.\n\n- [ ] The 30-plan FP-control gate result is committed with the N=3 replication median, the null-replay\n  noise floor, and the R1 pass/fail decision. Proving:\n  `jq -e 'has(\"new_blocking_median\") and has(\"new_advisory_median_delta\") and has(\"null_floor_pass_to_block\") and (.replays|length==3) and has(\"r1_pass\")' docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/e3/<label>/fp_control.json`\n  (the median is `>3/30`-tested and `>1`-tested against the recorded `r1_pass` boolean, mirroring\n  SOTA ¬ß5/R1).\n\n- [ ] The E3 method is documented in `runs/README.md`, covering the baseline source + chosen round, the\n  cleanly-closed filter, the material-fingerprint drift control, the INDETERMINATE-exclusion rule, and\n  the LLM-nondeterminism control with its billable-cost note. Proving:\n  `grep -q \"material_fingerprint\" docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/README.md && grep -q \"cleanly-closed\" docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/README.md && grep -q \"all_review_results\" docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/README.md`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784260820806098001,"uuid":"565e5e73-ea90-4a74-85f2-2daa1ca75a4f"}